1
00:00:00,333 --> 00:00:06,208
After exactly 16 days

2
00:00:07,583 --> 00:00:09,416
My brother was released

3
00:00:10,208 --> 00:00:12,041
Along with the young man who was with me

4
00:00:12,333 --> 00:00:14,000
Who was from Daraa Province

5
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:15,916
And who used to say that he was with ISIS

6
00:00:16,458 --> 00:00:18,708
He claimed he was one of ISIS’s security members in Daraa

7
00:00:18,916 --> 00:00:21,916
And was detained after being suspected upon arriving in Raqqa

8
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:25,083
I had nothing personal to talk with him about

9
00:00:25,333 --> 00:00:28,125
The conversations we had were routine and ordinary

10
00:00:28,416 --> 00:00:30,625
They brought in his place a young man from Tabqa

11
00:00:31,875 --> 00:00:34,041
Who stayed with me for three days

12
00:00:34,291 --> 00:00:36,500
I asked him about the situation outside

13
00:00:36,750 --> 00:00:38,250
He had heard about my detention with my family

14
00:00:38,750 --> 00:00:42,833
I asked him who among my relatives
was still imprisoned or had been released

15
00:00:44,291 --> 00:00:46,625
He told me who had been released from prison

16
00:00:46,916 --> 00:00:49,333
According to him, it was me and two of my brothers

17
00:00:49,666 --> 00:00:51,875
My father, and two of my cousins who remained

18
00:00:52,958 --> 00:00:54,416
I could hear the voices of the others in prison

19
00:00:54,583 --> 00:00:56,666
But those whose voices disappeared

20
00:00:56,791 --> 00:00:58,500
I was very worried about what had happened to them

21
00:00:58,708 --> 00:01:01,791
He assured me that all those who had been released were fine

22
00:01:02,833 --> 00:01:08,791
They placed my brother in the prison corridor before sunset

23
00:01:09,166 --> 00:01:14,666
During the time when we usually received dinner

24
00:01:18,541 --> 00:01:22,083
My brother started talking to me and asking how I was

25
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:24,375
Taking advantage of the absence of anyone in the corridor

26
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:27,166
He told me he was going to be released

27
00:01:27,333 --> 00:01:28,750
Since it was customary to release prisoners

28
00:01:29,041 --> 00:01:31,166
Every Monday and Thursday

29
00:01:31,416 --> 00:01:33,583
But my brother’s release was on a Wednesday

30
00:01:35,041 --> 00:01:38,708
I asked him what he had told them, and he reassured me

31
00:01:38,916 --> 00:01:41,958
Telling me not to worry, that everything
was fine and he would be out soon

32
00:01:42,250 --> 00:01:44,208
My brother was four years older than me
